can I do it by uploading to google drive?

Yes, you can use Google Drive, but you can't use the standard "sharing link" directly in the code because that link leads to a Google Drive viewer page, not the raw image file itself.

To make it work, you need to convert your sharing link into a Direct Download Link.

Step 1: Get the Sharing Link

  1. Upload the image to Google Drive.

  2. Right-click the file > Share > Share.

  3. Under "General access," change it to "Anyone with the link."

  4. Click Copy link.

Step 2: Convert to Direct Link

Your copied link will look something like this: https://drive.google.com/file/d/FILE_ID/view?usp=sharing

Copy the FILE_ID (the long string of letters and numbers) and paste it into this format: https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/FILE_ID

Step 3: Update the Code

Replace the background-image URL in your flyer.html with your new converted link.

Note: The lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/ID method is the most reliable way to bypass Google's "preview" page and load the image directly into your design.
